      <bioghist id="ref2">
         <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
         <p>G. Edward Lewis (b. October 27, 1908, d. May 11, 1997). Yale PhB 1930, PhD 1937. Curator Vert. Paleo. 1939-45. On Yale geol. faculty 37-45. Later, geologist on U.S. Geol. Survey. Worked in Navel Intelligence during WWII. Discovered the first specimen of Ramapithecus as a graduate student working in the Siwalik Hills of India in the 1930s. Also took part in the American Museum-Sinclair Expedition in the 1930s, working as Barnum Brown's chief assistant and photographer.</p>  
      </bioghist>
